modules.description: This module implements low-level Ethernet I/O operations for network device interaction, including packet transmission and reception. It works with abstract handles to network interfaces (`t`), MAC addresses (`Macaddr.t`), and memory buffers (`Cstruct.t`). Concrete use cases include sending raw Ethernet frames with `write`, receiving packets via `listen`, retrieving interface metadata like `mac` and `mtu`, and managing connection state with `connect` and `disconnect`.
